Siemens’ Cybersecurity department has also acted to mitigate risk even more. For example:

→ As industrial environments become increasingly digi- talized, the share of software grows significantly, as does the number of associated vulnerabilities. To mitigate these risks, Siemens is automating the collection and distribution of information about vulnerabilities with the goal of offering end-to-end security for our customers. These efforts include our collaboration with the Common Security Advisory Framework (CSAF) 2.0 from the OASIS Consortium